Rheumatic complaints are common in patients with HIV, and HIV positivity confers 
an increased susceptibility in populations with similar risk factors for HIV 
infection. With the advent of the modern combined antiretroviral treatment, 
HAART has had a profound beneficial effect on survival in HIV-infected patients, 
with lifelong control of HIV infection and normalization of life expectancy; but 
