Patients typically lose more than 50% of their excess weight after bariatric 
surgery. Obesity-related diseases markedly improve, reducing cardiovascular risk 
and improving life expectancy. Obese patients lose more weight with bariatric 
surgery than with medical weight-loss treatment.

